						               													<description>This game is for pupils aged 8-9 years, studing the Mesopotamic Sumerian Civilization.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Farm your land, harvest your grain, build your city, commerce with your neighbours... it gives a taste of how the Mesopotamian agricolture and first cities worked.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is the king of one of the Sumerian cities of the title;  in every seasonal turn, the king must choose which building to build in its city, each building is represented by the tiles taken at the start of each turn. The king must carefully plan how to increase its city, in order to get enough food for each building; in case of famine, the building without enough food is destroyed! Building some particular buildings permit to commerce with the other cities during the game. The king building all the compulsory buildings, like royal palace or ziqqurat and some other optional buildings, wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Four maps, 2 pages rules, 110 small tokens are ready to print and play!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Il gioco &amp;egrave; dedicato agli alunni della scuola elementare che stanno studiano la civilt&amp;agrave; dei Sumeri.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Coltiva i tuoi campi, raccogli i frutti del tuo lavoro, ingrandisci la tua citt&amp;agrave;!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Intende simulare i rapporti tra le citt&amp;agrave; della Mezzaluna Fertile e la necessit&amp;agrave; di sviluppare l\'agricoltura per la sopravvivenza.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ogni giocatore &amp;egrave; il re di una delle citt&amp;agrave; sumere del titolo e deve ingrandire la propria citt&amp;agrave; costruendo gli edifici obbligatori, come la ziqqurat e alcuni di quelli non obbligatori, facendo attenzione ad avere abbastanza cibo per tutti!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Quattro carte, un regolamento di due pagine, 110 piccole carte da ritagliare completano il gioco.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
